results.name: Number of ways writing n^n as a product of decimal digits of some other number which has no digits equal to 1.
comment: a(n)= 0 when n has prime-factor larger than 7 [so A067734(n)=0] or when n is in A068191, i.e. not in A002473.
example: n=1 has no solution; a(2)=A000073(6)=2 with {4,22} solutions; a(3)=A067734(27)=3=Fibonacci[4]; n=5 and n=7, n^n has single prime factor of which any true multiple have 2 digits so 55555 and 7777777 are the only solutions, so a(5)=a(7)=1; a(4)=A067734(256)=81=A000073(10); a(8)=A067734(2^24)=A000073(26)=1389537; n=9 a(9)=A067734(3^27)=Fibonacci(28)=A000045(28)=317811.
